Arsene Wenger anger at Belgium's treatment of Vermaelen
Media playback is not supported on this deviceArsenal manager Arsene Wenger vents his anger at the Belgian FA's use of Thomas Vermaelen in their friendly on Wednesday,threatening to take actionagainst the federation.The 26-year-old defender played 90 minutes in the friendly against Greece despite carrying an injury and is a doubt forSaturday's Premier Leaguetrip to Liverpool.